As a result hair gathers and reflects the light, giving it a spectacular shine. This exquisite mixture has a pleasant silky texture that absorbs into the hair rapidly leaving no residue on the scalp or hair. The delicious Amber fragrance with a base of Vanilla will transport you into a fascinating world of oriental perfume. Keratin delivers the perfect weightless infusion of keratin protein, a natural conditioner that prevents breakage and alleviates split ends. It absorbs quickly without feeling heavy or greasy, and smooths the hair's surface for a reflective, shiny finish and stunning sheen. Argan Oil comes from the Argan tree in Morocco and dates back millions of years. Rich in vitamin E and provides a natural protection for your hair leaving it feeling light and incredibly nourished, its special properties are also effective in soothing itchy scalps. Linseed Oil is derived from the tiny seeds of the flax plant in the Mediterranean. Containing Omega 3 and unsaturated fatty acids it seals and smoothes the cuticles of the hair providing uniformity and control. Directions of use: For Styling and Finishing: Apply a small amount onto your palms and work through damp hair after shampooing. Style as usual. For Protection: Apply a small amount to dry hair to protect from damage caused by sun, wind and other harsh environmental factors. For Colour & Chemical Treatment: Before applying colour, highlights, straightening or relaxer chemical treatments, prepare hair by applying approximately 5ml directly onto hair and gently massage. Made by Monks, the incense is created by crushing and mixing various natural ingredients - often dozens of them - into a paste and rolling the paste into the thick sticks. Tibetan incense also has less smell to it until it is burned and the fragrance is much more pure.Because of the thickness, they will not fit into most of the traditional (boat, coffin, wheel, etc.) incense holders.
